# PII redaction (outgoing LLM traffic)
presidio-analyzer>=2.2    # Pattern recognizers only (credit card Luhn, IBAN checksum)
onnxruntime>=1.26.0
# Neural PII is currently disabled in practice — `optimum 1.17.1`'s
# `optimum.utils.input_generators` does
#     from transformers.utils import is_tf_available, is_torch_available
# but that symbol is gone from every transformers version we have access
# to (5.7.0, 5.8.x, 5.9.x). `apps.pii.engine.get_pii_pipeline()` catches
# the ImportError and falls back to Presidio pattern recognizers — that's
# the production behavior on the canary today. Restoring neural PII
# requires either an upstream optimum fix (>=2.x drops the broken import)
# or our own engine refactor; tracked as a separate piece of work.
#
# Until then: keep the pin range that origin/main runs (so we don't
# stir up a new pip resolution), and lean on the dependabot ignore in
# .github/dependabot.yml to prevent further drift across this whole
# triplet (transformers / optimum / onnxruntime).
transformers>=5.9.0,<5.10.0
